The paper deals with the design of Convolutional Networks (ConvNets) for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel differentiable Neural Architecture Search (NAS) formulation, which involves optimizing the architecture of the ConvNet, and this falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses hyperparameter optimization techniques to find the best trade-off between accuracy and runtime, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which falls under the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
